summary: This is an email from an FBI Special Agent in New York transmitting a federal grand jury subpoena to Southwest Airlines, requesting records by February 7, 2020, for a child exploitation/human trafficking investigation. The email instructs the recipient not to notify the subscriber due to the sensitive nature of the investigation.

persons.name: Special Agent
persons.context: The FBI Special Agent from the New York Child Exploitation & Human Trafficking unit who sent the email transmitting the grand jury subpoena to Southwest Airlines and requested expedited cooperation.

events.title: Subpoena Due Date
events.description: The expedited due date by which Southwest Airlines must comply with the federal grand jury subpoena for records.

events.title: Subpoena Transmission
events.description: An FBI Special Agent emails a federal grand jury subpoena to Southwest Airlines regarding a child exploitation/human trafficking investigation.

keyFacts: A federal grand jury subpoena was issued to Southwest Airlines as part of a child exploitation/human trafficking investigation.
The subpoena had an expedited due date of February 7, 2020, indicating urgency in the investigation.
The FBI requested that Southwest Airlines not notify the subscriber of the subpoena due to the sensitive nature of the investigation.
The communication originated from the FBI's New York Child Exploitation & Human Trafficking unit.
